## Step 1: About Dataset and Network

#The data utilized for this case is a data set on movie characters.Eight movies were considered alongside seven actors. The movies considered inthe data are Central Intelligence, Red Notice, Aquaman, Justice League, Fastand Furious; Hobbs and Shaw, Bloodshot, Fate of the Furious and Fast and Furious 4. The actors considered are Dwayne Johnson, Kevin Hart, Ryan Reynolds, Gal Gadot, Jason Momoa, Elza Gonzalez and Vin Diesel. The network will be createdbased on the movies in which the actors appear together.

#The unit for analysis in the network will be such that actors will form the nodes and the movies in which actors appear together will form the edges.

#Loading Data

Movie_SNA_Data <- read.csv("/Users/codyxu/R/Movie_Characters_Data.csv",row.names = 1)

#Visualizing  Network

Movie_Net <- graph_from_adjacency_matrix(as.matrix(Movie_SNA_Data), weighted=TRUE, mode="undirected")
plot(Movie_Net)

## Step 3: Global Network Properties
#From the result below, the number of nodes in the network is 7 with the number of edges being 13. The density of the network is 61.91% implying that the networkis 61.91% complete, while the diameter of the network is 2.
#Number of Nodes
vcount(Movie_Net)
## [1] 7
#nUmber of edges
ecount(Movie_Net)
## [1] 13
#Density
d <- edge_density(Movie_Net)
d
## [1] 0.6190476
#Diameter
diameter(Movie_Net)
## [1] 2
## Step 4: Vertices Description 

#The check on the degree centrality produced the results below. The results show that at degree = 6, Dwayne Johnson is the most important member of the network.

#Degree Centrality
degree(Movie_Net)
## Dwayne.Johnson     Kevin.Hart  Ryan.Reynolds      Gal.Gadot    Jason.Momoa 
##              6              3              4              4              2 
##  Elza.Gonzalex     Vin.Diesel 
##              4              3
#The check on the closeness centrality produced the results below. The results show that at closeness = 1, Dwayne Johnson is the member of the network that can quickly reach other members of the network.
#Closeness Centrality
closeness(Movie_Net, normalized = T)
## Dwayne.Johnson     Kevin.Hart  Ryan.Reynolds      Gal.Gadot    Jason.Momoa 
##      1.0000000      0.6666667      0.7500000      0.7500000      0.6000000 
##  Elza.Gonzalex     Vin.Diesel 
##      0.7500000      0.6666667
#The check on the betweenness centrality produced the results below. The results show that at betweeness = 1, Dwayne Johnson is the member of the network that is most influential.

#Betweeness Centrality
betweenness(Movie_Net, directed = F, normalized = T)
## Dwayne.Johnson     Kevin.Hart  Ryan.Reynolds      Gal.Gadot    Jason.Momoa 
##     0.31111111     0.00000000     0.05555556     0.08888889     0.00000000 
##  Elza.Gonzalex     Vin.Diesel 
##     0.05555556     0.02222222
## Step 5: Community Detection

#The community detection in this network detected two communities with community 1 having 3 actors and community 2 having 4 actors.The network displaying the communities is given below. 

#Community Detection
fc <- cluster_fast_greedy(Movie_Net)
membership(fc)
## Dwayne.Johnson     Kevin.Hart  Ryan.Reynolds      Gal.Gadot    Jason.Momoa 
##              2              1              1              2              2 
##  Elza.Gonzalex     Vin.Diesel 
##              1              2
#Checking community sizes
sizes(fc)
## Community sizes
## 1 2 
## 3 4
#Plotting communities
V(Movie_Net)$color <- fc$membership
plot(Movie_Net)

## Step 6: Discussion 
#With the highest degree centrality, closeness centrality and between centrality, Dwayne Johnson represents the most notable actor with high likelihood offeaturing in superhero and crime movies.

## Step 8: Conclusion
#In conclusion, the network analysis of the eight superhero and crime movies for the seven actors has shown that out of the seven actors, Dwayne Johnson is able to play roles comfortably in both crime and superhero movies.
